        <updateDate>2018-05-09T21:24:01Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Transportation and Trailer Modernization Act of 2017</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Clean Air Act to revise the definition of a motor vehicle to exclude trailers and vehicles reliant on a connection to a self-propelled vehicle for power. (The Environmental Protection Agency set emissions standards for trailers as a part of motor vehicle emissions regulations. The regulations as applied to trailers were stayed by a federal court on October 27, 2017.) </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
